A^2 = \begin{bmatrix} 0 & 1 \\                                 -1 & 0 \end{bmatrix}
A (2 \times 2)
[a=\left[\begin{matrix}\cos \beta & -\sin \beta \\ \sin \beta & \cos \beta \end{matrix}\right]\\then\\a^2=\left[\begin{matrix}\cos 2\beta & -\sin 2\beta \\ \sin 2\beta & \cos 2\beta \end{matrix}\right]\\now \\a^2=\left[\begin{matrix}0 & 1 \\-1 & 0 \end{matrix}\right]\\now\\sin 2\beta=-1 ,\cos 2\beta=0 \\beta=\frac{ 3\pi }{ 4}\\a=\left[\begin{matrix}\cos \beta & -\sin \beta \\ \sin \beta & \cos \beta  \end{matrix}\right]
